sentence: Technology shares were lower in pre-market trade Monday with several more earnings reports in this sector.
In technology stocks news, Seagate Technology ( STX ) reported Q1 earnings of $1.34 per share, well ahead of the analyst consensus of $1.25 per share on Capital IQ.
Revenue came in at $3.78 billion, better than expectations of $3.62 billion.
The results were up from year ago levels of $1.29 per share in earnings and $3.48 billion in revenue.

And, Roper Industries ( ROP ), a provider of radio-frequency products, services and application software, Monday reported Q3 adjusted earnings above the Street view despite a slight revenue miss, and boosted its full-year earnings guidance.
Net earnings rose to $155.5 million, or $1.54 per dluted share, from $136.3 million, or $1.36 per diluted share, a year earlier.

Adjusted to exclude one-time items, its diluted earnings per share were $1.55 in the latest quarter, up from $1.42 a year earlier and topping the $1.53 expected on average by analysts polled by Capital IQ.
ROP was inactive in recent pre-market trading after closing Friday at $151.18, in a 52-week range of $123.18 to $151.74.

Finally, Salesforce.com ( CRM ), which provides cloud computing and social enterprise solutions, is making a major push into the healthcare industry and is betting on replacing outmoded medical industry infrastructure, Reuters reported, citing two people briefed on the plans.
The shares were up 0.3% pre-market at $59.75 and have a 52-week spread of $48.18 - $67.00.
